Package: RmdHelpers
Title: Add text to multiple Rmd outputs simultaneously, including LaTeX and Word
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Ezra", "Moses", , "moses8@illinois.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Compact functions to aid in inserting formatted text (colored font, altered fontface, lists, etc.) into multiple Rmd outputs. The idea is that you only need to supply the formatting you'd like applied (as a function from this package) and the text you'd like the formatting applied to (as the arguments passed to the function), and the rest is handled by the functions themselves. No need for lengthy if/else code blocks in your Rmd files, as these functions do all that heavy lifting for you. Particularly useful for dual LaTeX and Word outputs, which often have different syntax for basic document operations.
